name: Pratibimb
desc: The cultural extravaganza of VJTI, filled with joy and innumerable memories, Pratibimb is a  reflection of pulsating energy, infectious enthusiasm, heartwarming fellowship, winning attitudes, crazy moments, and wonderful times! It continues to provide an attractive platform for showcasing the fresh talent that college students have within them. Spanning three fun-filled days of the festival, there are contests and workshops, encompassing everything from art to music and dance. For those who like an intellectual challenge, there is a range of events to test their skills in the literary arts and managerial area. Pratibimb is the annual national-level cultural extravaganza of VJTI, which musters a huge enthusiastic crowd every year. Many events add to the glory of Pratibimib. Illuminati is the inter branch competition at Pratibimb VJTI. All the branches engage in a fierce battle against each other via tasks allocated to them during the course of the year. These tasks span over a variety of genres. Right from art and craft to singing, dancing, drama, quizzes and many many more. All the students zealously participate in all these events to bag points for their branch and the branch with the most points at the end of the 4 day cultural festival wins the prestigious Illuminati Cup. This year's theme for Illuminati is 'Turn it into Art.' Mumbai’s Got Talent - Talent from the City of Dreams, comes on the vibrant stage of Pratis very own Mumbai’s Got Talent. Dancers, Musicians, Acrobats and performers showcase their talent and zest, in this event. Groove to the rhythms of music, immerse yourself in those nights and etch countless memories in your heats with the amazing concerts of Pratibimb.

events.edescription: After having successfully represented your branch, it's time to compete against one another Yes!! It's time for the DC/SR wars!!

name: Technovanza
desc: Technovanza, the premiere technical group initiative of the VJTI Social Group, is one of Asia's Largest Techno-Manegerial Festival; boasting a gigantic footfall of 75000+ consisting of 40% corporate and executive crowd, the student body crowd covering 500+ colleges and an equally staggering digital presence of approximately 70,000+ social media followers. Our prime time motto, 'Taking Technology to Society'​, one that was bestowed upon us by The 11th President of India Late Dr. A P J Abdul Kalam, has been the founding stone on which the slabs of scientific acumen, the walls of healthy competition and the finishing paint of technological excellence have rendered the extravagant structure of an enhancing student body. A groundbreaking line up of outstanding speakers, both international and domestic, every year at the VJTI Guest Lecture Series, is the cherry on top of the cake of insight. Equally stringent have been Technovanza's efforts to spark unrestrained, yet healthy competition between participants over the expanse of 20+ events. Technovanza intends to bring it's theme into rightful application, which is precisely why the community has been a premiere homeground for social initiatives like Mission Mumbai and Pratigya, to enhance the quality of human resource dwelling in the world of today.

name: Rangawardhan
desc: Rangawardhan VJTI is a Marathi cultural group working for preservation and promotion of Marathi culture and language for the past 21 years. This festival encourages growth of Maharashtrian culture and appreciation of Marathi artists and dignitaries who did commendable work in their field. Marathi actors are invited and appreciated for their work. Rangawardhan has engraved its name in Mumbai’s most popular cultural events, adding to more than 10k footfall for the festival every year. It has encouraged Marathi literature and arranged various events for Marathi poetry, drama, street plays, folk dance, one act plays, music etc.

events.edescription: Rangvardhan, who has been glorifying Marathi for many years, is all set to create a new history in 2022-23. Marathi BIG BOSS Mahesh Manjrekar sir witnessed the opening ceremony of this golden season. After that, Natyavardhan's one act Harlequin gave a new zest to the opening! Done and a new Marathi chapter started.

Rangawardhan VJTI is a Marathi cultural group working for preservation and promotion of Marathi culture and language for the past 21 years. This festival encourages growth of Maharashtrian culture and appreciation of Marathi artists and dignitaries who did commendable work in their field. Marathi actors are invited and appreciated for their work. Rangawardhan has engraved its name in Mumbai’s most popular cultural events, adding to more than 10k footfall for the festival every year. It has encouraged Marathi literature and arranged various events for Marathi poetry, drama, street plays, folk dance, one act plays, music etc. Rangawardhan has been graced by the scintillating presence of influential Marathi artists, actors, sportspersons, singers. Some of them were honorable social worker Sindhu Tai Sapkal, Dr. Prakash Baba Amte, actors and Marathi film directors like Mahesh Kothare, Sandeep Pathak, Vijay Pathkar, Sunil Barve, Subodh Bhave. Rangawardhan has hosted many influential personalities like Mr.Vishwas Nangre Patil, Dr. Jayant Narlikar, Supriya Sule. Rangawardhan has also hosted a lot of successful events and was sponsored by renowned organizations like Sakal, LIC, Samana, Maharashtra Times, TIME, SBI, Sharechat, m-indicator, Maiboli marathi channel, Canon and a lot more. Rangawardhan has witnessed graceful participation of students.

name: DLA
desc: DLA stands for Debate and Literary Activities Club of VJTI.It is an extremely chill, close-knit community of like-minded individuals who share a common interest in debates, books, performing arts and similar activities. DLA is a place where your thoughts meet paper, where your ideas meet fruition, where your opinions find a voice, and where literature meets a unique sense of humor. DLA also hosts a multitude of events in the field of literary and performing arts to cultivate a community of passionate individuals who ardently share their enthusiasm for literature.To mark a step forward, this year, DLA held its very first Fest (i e) the LitFest and was honored by the presence of our phenomenal guest, Ms. Ami Ganatra who is an author, a devout yoga practitioner and a student of sanskrit and Indian Knowledge systems at the inaugural year of Litfest.
dates: The Litfest was held on 19,20,21 and 22nd of Jan, 2023.

events.edescription: DLA provides a platform to all the students from VJTI and beyond to exhibit their talent in the Open Mic. Multitude of performances ranging from poetry, stand ups, story telling, singing and band performances are encouraged and promoted here.

Book Club is a place for all the bibliophiles across the campus to meet and offer their perspectives and have healthy conversations over an amazing book of everyone's choice. While there, you can share your thoughts and opinions, get intellectually stimulated and have loads and loads of fun !

It is one of the most sought after and anticipated events where all the quizzing enthusiasts from the freshers bid against each other to answer questions from all the domains like current affairs, sports, food, films, fictions, history etc. The FY Quiz plays a key role in the resurgence of quizzing and other literary events in VJTI.

M.U.N. stands for Model United Nations. It is an academic simulation of the United Nations where students play the role of delegates from different countries and attempt to resolve real world issues with the policies and perspectives of their assigned country.\nVJMUN provides an excellent opportunity to discuss and debate awesome topics ranging from politics, human rights to deescalating wars ! Exposure to top debaters adds an important skill to your skillset.\nVJMUN has stood the test of time, making it one  of the oldest MUNs in Mumbai today. Generations have joined and left feeling satisfied and more confident than ever before. An active MUN delegation only means excellent exposure to all the veterans that have come before us !

name: Enthusia
desc: Enthusia, the premier sports committee of one of the prime colleges of Mumbai and Maharashtra, VJTI (Veermata Jijabai Technological Institute), currently the th 4th largest sports festival in India. We, at VJTI, are fortunate to have a basketball court, cricket ground, football ground, and an indoor and outdoor Gymnasium. ENTHUSIA is the annual grand level sports fest which attracts about 20-25k people from 100 different colleges accross the state. Our prime motto, “We are One Team putting our efforts into One Heart to maintain  One Legacy of excellence in sports. From getting inspired from 'Milka Singh' to being the building stone on laying the slabs of sports in our prestigious college in 2009.  2023 being the 14th  year of pride in sports run by the extravagant structure of the enhancing student body.  Enthusia main aim is to spark free and healthy competition over an expanse of 15+ events which tests the ability of the studints to prove their dedication to winning and strategise about execution which will without a doubt make them the best of all. We organise a marathon and a cyclothon every year to raise awareness about different important issues in the country. For a college based festival that is made by the students for the students, Enthusia welcomes everyone who wishes to be a part of this fun filled event that will intends to bring the community together through sports.

name: Digital VJTI
desc: Digital VJTI is the golden string which woves all our jewels, our committees together.This committee is the backend of VJTI Social Group and hosts numerous activities with its collaboration. Digital VJTI is a budding platform for content creators, video editors and photographers to thrive. It also holds workshops on this skillsets for beginners who want to be a part of this amazing space.Digital VJTI assists other committees in video editing, poster designing and creating social media posts.The talented photographers of Digital VJTI cover all the events and gatherings of other committees.

name: E-Cell
desc: E-Cell VJTI strives to be at the forefront by promoting entrepreneurship as a career, creating holistic and synergistic environment required to inculcate strong entrepreneurial spirit in students.We at E-CELL VJTI aim to facilitate interaction between individuals with creative minds and ideas with potential for substantial business opportunities and to enable smooth and efficient interaction between its principal components spanning students, faculty, working professionals, aspiring and existing entrepreneurs, mentors, angel investors and venture capitalists.

events.edescription: Adomania is an E-cell industrial advertisement marketing event that focuses on the marketing strategy of a particular product of a company. This managerial event will provide you with an opportunity to be “the ADMAN “of the real world organization for a day.
A One stop destination where startups, mentors, investors, corporates and students from across India come together to transact business, pitch for funding and share experiences.
The national level business plan competition. It takes them right from initial idea formulation stage to the stage of investment and execution.
